The numbers are placed on a hexagonal lattice by spiralling outward from 1.
For a hexagonal spiral the maximal number in the \(k^{\text{th}}\) ring is  

\[
N_{\max }(k)=1+3k(k+1), \qquad k=0,1,2,\dots
\]

Hence the ring containing \(2026\) satisfies  

\[
N_{\max }(25)=1951<2026\le N_{\max }(26)=2107 ,
\]

so \(2026\) lies in ring \(k=26\).

---

### 1.  Coordinates of \(2026\)

Number \(n\) in ring \(k\) is at an offset  

\[
p=n-\bigl(N_{\max }(k-1)+1\bigr)
\]

from the first cell of the ring (the cell \((k,0)\) on the east side).  
For \(k=26\),

\[
\text{first number}=N_{\max }(25)+1=1952,
\qquad
p = 2026-1952 = 74 .
\]

The ring is walked in six straight segments, each of length \(k\), in the
directions  

\[
(0,-1),\;(-1,0),\;(-1,1),\;(0,1),\;(1,0),\;(1,-1).
\]

Since \(p=74\) lies in the third segment (\(52\le p\le77\)),
the coordinate of \(2026\) is  

\[
(-22,-4).
\]

---

### 2.  The six neighbours

Adding the six axial neighbour‑vectors gives the six neighbour coordinates:

\[
\begin{aligned}
&(-21,-4),\;(-21,-5),\;(-22,-5),\\
&(-23,-4),\;(-23,-3),\;(-22,-3).
\end{aligned}
\]

Each of these coordinates belongs to a specific ring; using the same
spiral‑ordering rule we convert them back to their numbers.

| coordinate | ring \(k\) | segment | offset in ring | number |
|------------|------------|---------|----------------|--------|
| \((-21,-4)\) | 25 | segment 2 (\(-i,-k+i\)) with \(i=21\) | \(2k+i=71\) | \(1802+71=1873\) |
| \((-21,-5)\) | 26 | segment 2, \(i=21\) | \(2k+i=73\) | \(1952+73=2025\) |
| \((-22,-5)\) | 27 | segment 2, \(i=22\) | \(2k+i=76\) | \(2108+76=2184\) |
| \((-23,-4)\) | 27 | segment 2, \(i=23\) | \(2k+i=77\) | \(2108+77=2185\) |
| \((-23,-3)\) | 26 | segment 2, \(i=23\) | \(2k+i=75\) | \(1952+75=2027\) |
| \((-22,-3)\) | 25 | segment 2, \(i=22\) | \(2k+i=72\) | \(1802+72=1874\) |

Thus the six neighbours of \(2026\) are  

\[
1873,\;2025,\;2184,\;2185,\;2027,\;1874 .
\]

---

### 3.  Their sum

\[
\begin{aligned}
1873+1874 &= 3747,\\
2025+2027 &= 4052,\\
2184+2185 &= 4369,\\[2pt]
\text{Total} &= 3747+4052+4369 = 12168 .
\end{aligned}
\]

\[
\boxed{12168}
\]
